Author: chpbnvic
Text: About 10 years ago is when I first lost a lot of weight. I ate apples everyday. I can’t really eat plain apples anymore.

Author: thisaintheavymetal
Text: hmm. sort of! i can relate to the coffee drink thing for sure, but i’m not sure i can relate to being “bored” of foods i’m familiar with. i guess i sort of become indifferent to foods that i liked before developing an ED/when i restrict higher, like something that is kinda low calorie but not low calorie enough. i just see it in the fridge and disregard it and forget that it exists. with high calorie foods though... that i can’t seem to forget about. its like mid-level foods if that makes sense.
